modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and generating JSON data using the YAJL library. Operates on strings, buffers, and OCaml values with support for streaming and incremental processing. Used to efficiently handle large JSON inputs and convert OCaml data structures to JSON format.

The module offers JSON parsing and generation functionalities, utilizing callback-based processing and buffer manipulation to handle input and output. It works with primitive data types like strings, integers, and floats, alongside structured JSON formats, while enabling customization through configurable options and typed callback interfaces. This supports use cases such as real-time data serialization, custom parsing logic, and efficient memory management in applications requiring flexible JSON handling.
